# President duties

The role of the President is to:

* Act as chairperson of the board of directors
* Preside at all membership meetings
* Present at each annual general meeting an annual report of the work of the organization
* Appoint all committees (temporary or permanent)
* See that all books, reports and certificates as required by law are properly kept or filed
* Be one of the officers who may sign the checks or drafts of the organization
* Have such powers as may be reasonably construed as belonging to the chief executive of any organization

## Record keeping

SPI's records are all in electronic form.  When a contract or other
agreement is signed, it should be stored in the `board-private` Git
repository.

